714676f-a.title: Manhattan: 85th Street (East) - 1st Avenue
714676f-a.text:
(1)
410-418 East 85th Street, south side, east of First Ave. The
building with the gravestones in front is a frame structure.
About 1916.
(2)
A close view of No. 412, the frame house shown above, about
sixteen years later.
1932.
J. Clarence Davies Collection, Museum of the City of New York.
Nemative No. 226.
(3)
The same, from a different angle.
September 23, 1935.
P. L. Sperr.
